ml.alternet.parser.ast

Interface TokenMapper<Node>

  • Type Parameters:
    Node - The type of the target node.

    public interface TokenMapper<Node>
    Maps a token value to a custom user node. A token marked as Grammar.Fragment doesn't need a mapper.
    Author:
    Philippe Poulard

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Node transform(ValueStack<TreeHandler.Value<Node>> stack, EventsHandler.TokenValue<?> token, Deque<TreeHandler.Value<Node>> next)
      Transform a token to a node in the context of what was previously parsed in the stack, and what follows in the current rule.

    • Method Detail

      • transform

        Node transform(ValueStack<TreeHandler.Value<Node>> stack,
               EventsHandler.TokenValue<?> token,
               Deque<TreeHandler.Value<Node>> next)
        Transform a token to a node in the context of what was previously parsed in the stack, and what follows in the current rule. For example, if a rule defines a comma-separated list of digits, that the input is "1,2,3,4", and that the current token is "2", then the next elements are ",3,4" and the stack is "1,". Some elements may be consumed during the production of the target node.
        Parameters:
        stack - The stack contains source tokens encountered so far but not yet processed. The stack is a work area that may be useful for the transformation of the token.
        token - The actual token value to transform is supplied by the parser.
        next - The next elements in the boundaries of the current rule.
        Returns:
        A custom user node, or null to keep the token unchanged (in that case it is supposed to be consumed elsewhere.
